 Lloren-Saryrn wrote:&lt;BR&gt;I am a pet class, necromancer, and I can reproduce this in MPG on Saryrn. Since I have had this happen many times now I have it down to a science. If you want an example, feel free to ask me in game. I'll be happy to surprise more unsuspecting wizards in the name of science! :-)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;_How to reliably reproduce this:_&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;1&amp;gt; Go to the hub of MPG.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:14:39 2006] You have entered Muramite Provinggrounds.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;2&amp;gt; Clear the mobs, leaving some corpses for your &lt;I&gt;Army of the Dead&lt;/I&gt; AA ability (3 should be sufficient).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;3&amp;gt; Wait for a mob to be pulled by your puller, wake the dead, send in your pet, then have a wizard cast a &lt;I&gt;rain&lt;/I&gt;-type spell on the mob such that the pets are in the AoE.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:31 2006] Skullet tells the group, 'an elite kyv hunter incoming!!!'&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:37 2006] You begin casting Army of the Dead.&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:39 2006] Jaseker tells you, 'Attacking an elite kyv hunter Master.'&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:41 2006] an elite kyv hunter's corpse rises to serve Lloren.&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:42 2006] an elite kyv hunter's corpse rises to serve Lloren.&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:43 2006] a lightning warrior diodite's corpse rises to serve Lloren.&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:44 2006] Ulzarra begins to cast a spell. &lt;TEARS Sun the of&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;4&amp;gt; Sit back in horror as your group's wizard is eaten by all the pets (including faithful Jaseker) in a matter of moments.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:49 2006] Jaseker tries to slash Ulzarra, but Ulzarra's magical skin absorbs the blow!&lt;BR&gt;... (more hits by Jaseker suppressed) ...&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:50 2006] Ulzarra hit Lloren`s pet for 2920 points of non-melee damage.&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:50 2006] Ulzarra delivers a critical blast! (2920)&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:52 2006] Lloren`s pet tries to hit Ulzarra, but Ulzarra's magical skin absorbs the blow!&lt;BR&gt;... (more hits by Lloren`s pet(s) suppressed) ...&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:22:53 2006] Skullet`s warder tries to slash Ulzarra, but Ulzarra's magical skin absorbs the blow!&lt;BR&gt;... (yeah, same here too) ...&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:23:01 2006] You tell your party, 'What the heck?'&lt;BR&gt;[Sat Jan 07 18:23:05 2006] Skullet tells the group, 'uhhm'&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;_Things that you can use to clear agro I have found thus far:_&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;1&amp;gt; Suspend your minion and resummon it. That seems to clear it permanently.&lt;BR&gt;2&amp;gt; /pet back off, /pet as you were. This seems to work if you spam it a few times to make the pet forget the wizard.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
